// Bun Snapshot v1, https://bun.sh/docs/test/snapshots

exports[`claude-to-codex CLI writes migrated files and emits the report only when requested 1`] = `
"# Root Claude

- Read \`CLAUDE.md\` and \`CLAUDE.local.md\` before editing.
- Hidden project guidance lives in \`.claude/CLAUDE.md\`.
- Shared skills live in \`.agents/skills\` and \`.agents/skills/release/SKILL.md\`.
- Legacy commands live in \`.agents/skills/review/SKILL.md\`.
- Subagents live in \`.codex/agents/reviewer.toml\`.
- Nested package guidance lives in \`packages/api/CLAUDE.md\`.
- Leave \`.claude/rules/testing.md\` alone.

## Prose references (for migration rewrites)

- The root instructions file AGENTS.md is canonical.
- Optional machine-specific rules go in AGENTS.override.md.
- Hidden-scope notes live at .agents/AGENTS.md before you run the sync tool.
- Nested packages may ship packages/api/AGENTS.md beside their code.
"
`;

exports[`claude-to-codex CLI writes migrated files and emits the report only when requested 2`] = `
"---
name: release
description: Run the project release workflow.
argument-hint: "[version]"
disable-model-invocation: true
allowed-tools: Read, Bash
model: sonnet
context: fork
agent: Explore
hooks:
  post-run: echo done
---

Use \`CLAUDE.md\` for the high level workflow.
Skim AGENTS.md again before you publish.
Read \`.agents/skills/release/references/checklist.md\` before starting.
If you need a reviewer, see \`.codex/agents/reviewer.toml\`.
Do not rewrite \`.claude/rules/testing.md\`.
Run \`\${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/scripts/release.sh\` with \`$ARGUMENTS\`.
"
`;
